
[1]segment

   SEG'MENT, n. [L. segmentum, from seco, to cut off.]

   1. In geometry, that part of the circle contained between a chord and
   an arch of that circle, or so much of the circle as is cut off by the
   chord.

   2. In general, a part cut off or divided; as the segments of a calyx.
